**Fixes:** #94716 — `CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION = "2.1.75"` is stale in two places; both send the wrong version in `user-agent: claude-cli/2.1.75` on every Anthropic OAuth request.

## Root cause

Two independent stale constants, both hardcoded to `"2.1.75"`:

| File | Symbol | User-agent path |
|---|---|---|
| `src/llm/providers/anthropic.ts:102` | `claudeCodeVersion` | OAuth bearer path (legacy SDK provider) |
| `src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.ts:62` | `CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION` | Managed Anthropic transport (native SSE) |

Every Anthropic OAuth-authenticated request from either code path sends `user-agent: claude-cli/2.1.75` regardless of the installed claude CLI version.

## Changes

**`src/llm/utils/claude-code-version.ts`** (new) — single source of truth, resolved once at module load:
```typescript
function resolveClaudeCodeVersion(): string {
  try {
    const require = createRequire(import.meta.url);
    const pkgPath = require.resolve("claude/package.json");
    const raw = JSON.parse(readFileSync(pkgPath, "utf8")) as { version?: unknown };
    if (typeof raw.version === "string" && /^\d/.test(raw.version)) return raw.version;
  } catch {
    // claude not reachable via module resolution — use last-known-good fallback
  }
  return "2.1.75";
}
export const CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION = resolveClaudeCodeVersion();
```

Resolution strategy: walks the Node.js module resolution tree from the openclaw runtime to find `claude/package.json` (co-installed in the same global `node_modules`). Evaluated once at module load — not on the request path, no process spawning.

**`src/llm/providers/anthropic.ts`** — remove `execSync("claude --version")` and `getClaudeCodeVersion()` cache; import shared `CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION`.

**`src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.ts`** — remove stale `const CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION = "2.1.75"` (line 62); import shared `CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION`. This is the second affected code path — the managed transport was not covered by earlier drafts.

**`src/llm/utils/claude-code-version.test.ts`** (new) — verifies the exported constant matches `^\d+\.\d+`.

## Proof

Live run on Windows 11, openclaw v2026.6.8, claude CLI v2.1.177 (global npm install):

```
> node -e "
const {createRequire}=require('module');const {readFileSync}=require('fs');
const r=createRequire(require.resolve('openclaw/package.json'));
const pkg=JSON.parse(readFileSync(r.resolve('claude/package.json'),'utf8'));
console.log('resolved:',pkg.version);
"
resolved: 2.1.177
```

Both `anthropic.ts` and `anthropic-transport-stream.ts` now resolve to `2.1.177` at module load, so `user-agent: claude-cli/2.1.177` is sent on all Anthropic OAuth paths.

**Before:** `user-agent: claude-cli/2.1.75` (legacy SDK + managed transport)
**After:** `user-agent: claude-cli/2.1.177` (both paths, resolved from installed package)

## Files changed

- `src/llm/utils/claude-code-version.ts` — new shared resolver
- `src/llm/utils/claude-code-version.test.ts` — new test
- `src/llm/providers/anthropic.ts` — legacy SDK path: use shared constant
- `src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.ts` — managed transport: use shared constant

